# Mapping a debate

Relations connect claims into a picture of the debate. Three kinds are
formal — the engine verifies them and stamps holds or fails. Two are
informal — supports and presupposes are your judgments, recorded honestly
as assertions.

prop policy : The tax cut was enacted
prop growth : The economy grew

claim A : if policy then growth
claim B : not policy or growth
claim C : if growth then policy
claim D : policy and not growth

// Formal assertions — each one is checked:
A equivalent-to B
A contradicts D
D entails policy
B entails C

// Informal assertions — recorded, not checked:
"Voters reward incumbents for growth" supports C
A presupposes "a causal link from policy to growth"

// The whole picture:
map